I89. Special rules for former spouses

I19(a) General rule

I11Except as otherwise specifically provided in this section, the provisions of chapter 84 of title 5 shall apply in the case of an employee of the Agency who is subject to chapter 84 of title 5 and who has a former spouse (as defined in section 8401(12) of title 5) or a qualified former spouse.

I19(b) Definitions

I11For purposes of this section:

I79(1) Employee

I12The term ``employee'' means an employee of the Agency who is subject to chapter 84 of title 5, including an employee referred to in section 2152(a) of this title.

I79(2) Qualified former spouse

I12The term ``qualified former spouse'' means a former spouse of an employee or retired employee who_

I13(A) in the case of a former spouse whose divorce from such employee became final on or before December 4, 1991, was married to such employee for not less than 10 years during periods of the employee's service which are creditable under section 8411 of title 5, at least 5 years of which were spent outside the United States by both the employee and the former spouse during the employee's service with the Agency; and

I13(B) in the case of a former spouse whose divorce from such employee becomes final after December 4, 1991, was married to such employee for not less than 10 years during periods of the employee's service which are creditable under section 8411 of title 5, at least 5 years of which were spent by the employee outside the United States during the employee's service with the Agency or otherwise in a position the duties of which qualified the employee for designation by the Director under the criteria prescribed in section 2013 of this title.

I79(3) Pro rata share

I12The term ``pro rata share'' means the percentage that is equal to (A) the number of days of the marriage of the qualified former spouse to the employee during the employee's periods of creditable service under chapter 84 of title 5, divided by (B) the total number of days of the employee's creditable service.

I79(4) Spousal agreement

I12The term ``spousal agreement'' means an agreement between an employee, former employee, or retired employee and such employee's spouse or qualified former spouse that_

I13(A) is in writing, is signed by the parties, and is notarized;

I13(B) has not been modified by court order; and

I13(C) has been authenticated by the Director.

I79(5) Court order

I12The term ``court order'' means any court decree of divorce, annulment or legal separation, or any court order or court-approved property settlement agreement incident to such court decree of divorce, annulment, or legal separation.

