I67T1``SEC. 1006. TREATMENT OF INFORMATION RELATING TO NATIONAL SECURITY.

S5800

I21``(a) T4In GeneralK._(1) The Director of National Intelligence shall assume responsibility for the handling and disposition of any information related to the national security of the United States that is received, considered, or used by the Commission under this title.

I21``(2) Any information related to the national security of the United States that is provided to the Commission by a congressional intelligence committee may not be further provided or released without the approval of the chairman of such committee.

