I19(a) Short title

I11This section may be cited as the ``National Security Agency Voluntary Separation Act''.

I19(b) Definitions

I11For purposes of this section_

I12(1) the term ``Director'' means the Director of the National Security Agency; and

I12(2) the term ``employee'' means an employee of the National Security Agency, serving under an appointment without time limitation, who has been currently employed by the National Security Agency for a continuous period of at least 12 months prior to the effective date of the program established under subsection (c) of this section, except that such term does not include_

I13(A) a reemployed annuitant under subchapter III of chapter 83 or chapter 84 of title 5 or another retirement system for employees of the Government; or

I13(B) an employee having a disability on the basis of which such employee is or would be eligible for disability retirement under any of the retirement systems referred to in subparagraph (A).

I19(c) Establishment of program

I11Notwithstanding any other provision of law, the Director, in his sole discretion, may establish a program under which employees may, after October 1, 2000, be eligible for early retirement, offered separation pay to separate from service voluntarily, or both.

