I89. Multiyear national intelligence program

I19(a) Annual submission of multiyear national intelligence program

I11The Director of National Intelligence shall submit to the congressional committees specified in subsection (d) of this section each year a multiyear national intelligence program plan reflecting the estimated expenditures and proposed appropriations required to support that program. Any such multiyear national intelligence program plan shall cover the fiscal year with respect to which the budget is submitted and at least four succeeding fiscal years.

I19(b) Time of submission

I11The Director of National Intelligence shall submit the report required by subsection (a) of this section each year at or about the same time that the budget is submitted to Congress pursuant to section 1105(a) of title 31.

I19(c) Consistency with budget estimates

I11The Director of National Intelligence and the Secretary of Defense shall ensure that the estimates referred to in subsection (a) of this section are consistent with the budget estimates submitted to Congress pursuant to section 1105(a) of title 31 for the fiscal year concerned and with the estimated expenditures and proposed appropriations for the future-years defense program submitted pursuant to section 221 of title 10.

